recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Atomic Energy Community, and in particular  the second paragraph of Article 101 thereof,
Having regard to the draft Council decision submitted by the Commission  (1),
Whereas the European Energy Charter was signed on 17 December 1991 by the European Communities and  their Member States;
Whereas all the signatories to the European Energy Charter undertook to draw up an Energy Charter  Treaty in order to provide a secure and binding international legal framework for the principles  and objectives set out in that Charter;
Whereas the implementation of the European Energy Charter is of fundamental importance to Europe's  future, allowing the Commonwealth of Independent States and the countries of central and eastern  Europe to develop their energy potential, while helping to improve security of supply;
Whereas it is necessary to consolidate the initiative and the central role of the Community to  enable the latter to participate fully in the implementation of the Energy Charter Treaty;
Whereas the provisional application of the Energy Charter Treaty will help attain the objectives of  the European Atomic Energy Community;
Whereas these provisions of the Energy Charter Treaty should be applied by the European Atomic  Energy Community on a provisional basis,
